Use Insight Builder to Create an Insight

Create an insight using the user-friendly insight authoring tool. Insight Builder is a business-analyst-focused and user-friendly metrics authoring tool. Using the visual builder, you can generate the required datasets similar to the ones generated by using SQL. Use your created insight in segments or activation to enrich your data.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS
USER PERMISSION SET NEEDED
To use Insight Builder:	Data Cloud for Marketing Data Aware Specialist

Go to the Calculated Insights tab in Data Cloud and create an insight with the visual builder.

Go to the Calculated Insights tab in Data Cloud.
Click New.
Click Create with Builder.
You’re brought to a full-screen experience to author an insight using Insight Builder. Click Select Objects.
Type in the desired object in the box to add it to your Insight Builder Canvas. Note the object type when adding any object. Click Next. For example, if you want to create an insight using Insight Builder to understand customer purchase history, add Sales Order to the canvas, followed by history and purchasing frequency.

The chosen object is now available to build insights.

EXAMPLE Let’s consider a simple scenario where a business analyst want to aggregate the Product Sales by each Product from the Sales Order Data. Use the following sample DMO:
ORDERID	PRODUCTID	QUANTITY
13131	3131	23
To build the calculatedinsight for aggregating the Quantity by-product IDs, the business analyst creates an insight using the sales order object. Then selects the aggregate option, uses quality as the measures type, and Product ID as the dimension. After applying the measure, saving the expression, and running the insight job the business analysts gets the results they need.

Sample SQL expression:

SELECT ProductID, SUM(Quantity) as Total Quantity
FROM OrderDetails
Group by ProductID
